Therefore, the minimum of $P(x)$ occurs at $x = 1,$ so $P(x)$ is increasing.  Hence, $r$ and $s$ are the roots of $P(x) = 0$ such that $r < 1 < s.$

Then $r^3 + r = s^3 + s = 1,$ so
\[s^3 - r^3 = r - s.\]Then
\[(s - r)(s^2 + rs + r^2 - 1) = r - s.\]Since $s > r,$ $s^2 + rs + r^2 - 1 > 0.$  Hence, $s - r = \boxed{0}.$
